verses.text: Unto \w the|strong="H1732"\w* end, \w a|strong="H1732"\w* canticle \w of|strong="H1732"\w* \w a|strong="H1732"\w* \w psalm|strong="H4210"\w* \w of|strong="H1732"\w* \w the|strong="H1732"\w* resurrection. Shout \w with|strong="H1732"\w* joy \w to|strong="H1732"\w* God, all \w the|strong="H1732"\w* earth,
Sing ye \w a|strong="H0430"\w* psalm \w to|strong="H0430"\w* \w his|strong="H0430"\w* name; give glory \w to|strong="H0430"\w* \w his|strong="H0430"\w* \w praise|strong="H8416"\w*.

Say unto God, How terrible \w are|strong="H1320"\w* thy works, \w O|strong="H8085"\w* Lord! \w in|strong="H0935"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* multitude \w of|strong="H3605"\w* thy strength thy enemies \w shall|strong="H1320"\w* lie \w to|strong="H0935"\w* thee.

Let \w all|strong="H1697"\w* \w the|strong="H4480"\w* earth adore thee, \w and|strong="H1697"\w* sing \w to|strong="H1697"\w* thee: let it sing \w a|strong="H4480"\w* psalm \w to|strong="H1697"\w* thy name.

\w Come|strong="H7126"\w* \w and|strong="H1004"\w* see \w the|strong="H7126"\w* works \w of|strong="H1004"\w* God; who \w is|strong="H1004"\w* terrible \w in|strong="H1004"\w* \w his|strong="H7126"\w* counsels over \w the|strong="H7126"\w* sons \w of|strong="H1004"\w* \w men|strong="H0977"\w*.

\w Who|strong="H3605"\w* turneth \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w sea|strong="H3220"\w* \w into|strong="H0776"\w* dry \w land|strong="H0776"\w*, \w in|strong="H0430"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w river|strong="H0776"\w* \w they|strong="H3605"\w* \w shall|strong="H0776"\w* pass \w on|strong="H0776"\w* foot: \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w shall|strong="H0776"\w* \w we|strong="H3605"\w* rejoice \w in|strong="H0430"\w* \w him|strong="H3605"\w*.

Who \w by|strong="H3559"\w* \w his|strong="H3559"\w* \w power|strong="H1369"\w* ruleth \w for|strong="H3559"\w* ever: \w his|strong="H3559"\w* eyes behold \w the|strong="H3559"\w* nations; let \w not|strong="H3559"\w* them \w that|strong="H3559"\w* provoke him he exalted \w in|strong="H3559"\w* themselves.
O bless our God, ye Gentiles: \w and|strong="H3220"\w* make \w the|strong="H3220"\w* voice \w of|strong="H1995"\w* his praise \w to|strong="H3220"\w* \w be|strong="H3220"\w* heard.

\w Who|strong="H3427"\w* hath \w set|strong="H3427"\w* \w my|strong="H1242"\w* soul \w to|strong="H3427"\w* \w live|strong="H3427"\w*: \w and|strong="H1242"\w* hath not suffered \w my|strong="H1242"\w* feet \w to|strong="H3427"\w* \w be|strong="H3372"\w* moved:

\w For|strong="H3588"\w* thou, \w O|strong="H0430"\w* \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, hast proved \w us|strong="H3588"\w*: thou hast tried \w us|strong="H3588"\w* \w by|strong="H3559"\w* fire, \w as|strong="H3651"\w* silver \w is|strong="H0776"\w* tried.
Thou hast brought \w us|strong="H4127"\w* into \w a|strong="H5181"\w* net, thou hast laid afflictions \w on|strong="H7241"\w* \w our|strong="H1288"\w* back:

Thou hast set men over our heads. We \w have|strong="H8141"\w* passed through tire \w and|strong="H8141"\w* water, \w and|strong="H8141"\w* thou hast brought us out into \w a|strong="H8141"\w* refreshment.
I \w will|strong="H1389"\w* go into thy house \w with|strong="H2296"\w* burnt offerings: I \w will|strong="H1389"\w* pay thee my vows,

Which \w my|strong="H0637"\w* lips \w have|strong="H0637"\w* uttered, \w And|strong="H6629"\w* \w my|strong="H0637"\w* mouth hath spoken, when \w I|strong="H7891"\w* \w was|strong="H6629"\w* \w in|strong="H3847"\w* trouble.
I will offer up to thee holocausts full of marrow, with burnt offerings of rams: I will offer to thee bullocks with goats.
Come and hear, all ye that fear God, and I will tell you what great things he hath done for my soul.
I cried to him with my mouth: and I extolled him with my tongue.
If I have looked at iniquity in my heart, the Lord will not hear me.
Therefore hath God heard me, and hath attended to the voice of my supplication.
Blessed be God, who hath not turned away my prayer, nor his mercy from me.
